File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function var_student_t n,  Next: Function var_weibull a b,  Prev: Function var_rayleigh b,  Up: distrib

 -- Function: var_student_t (N)
     Returns the variance of a Student random variable t(n) , with n>2.

     The variance is

     V[X] = {n\over n-2}

     V[X] = {n\over n-2}

     (%i1) load ("distrib")$
     
     (%i2) var_student_t(n);
                                     n
     (%o2)                         -----
                                   n - 2


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function var_weibull a b,  Prev: Function var_student_t n,  Up: distrib

 -- Function: var_weibull (A, B)
     Returns the variance of a {\it Weibull}(a,b) random variable, with
     a,b>0.  To make use of this function, write first
     ‘load("distrib")’.

     The variance is

     V[X] = b^2\left[\Gamma\left(1+{2\over a}\right) -
     \Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)^2\right]

     V[X] = b^2\left[\Gamma\left(1+{2\over a}\right) -
     \Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)^2\right]


