File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function atan2 y x

 -- Function: atan2 (Y, X)
     - yields the value of \tan^{-1}(y/x) in the interval -\pi to \pi
     taking into consideration the quadrant of the point (x,y).

     Along the branch cut with y = 0 and x < 0, ‘atan2’ is continuous
     with the second quadrant.  See also ‘atan’.

     For variables that control simplification ‘_0025piargs’,
     ‘_0025iargs’, ‘halfangles’, ‘triginverses’, and ‘trigsign’.

     See also: ‘atan’, ‘%piargs’, ‘%iargs’, ‘halfangles’,
     ‘triginverses’, ‘trigsign’.


